</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR116:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR116"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              116-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 116</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Senator Alvarado-Gil<br/>(Coauthors: Senators Choi, Jones, Ochoa Bogh, Seyarto, and Valladares)<br/>(Coauthors: Assembly Members Alanis and Hadwick)<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 02, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to National School Choice Week.</span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 116, as introduced, Alvarado-Gil.
                          National School Choice Week.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate the week of January 25, 2026, to January 31, 2026, inclusive, as National School Choice Week.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_C7774E95-958E-487F-95E4-CC346EA3D3BC"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The California Constitution requires the Legislature to encourage by all suitable means the promotion of intellectual, scientific, moral, and agricultural improvement; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_330132C8-1456-47BD-B186-86663F9C795C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Excellence in education is a primary goal of the state and is essential to preparing pupils for civic participation, workforce readiness, and lifelong learning; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3EC5AE70-7355-43A2-ADF0-0D5BA9400598"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The state’s pupil body is one of the most diverse in the world, encompassing urban, suburban, rural, and agricultural communities, and, therefore, requires a diverse educational system; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E6572E24-A478-42AF-95AA-82FBE4D9306C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The state’s public education system includes a variety of instructional models, including traditional public schools, charter schools, and nonclassroom-based programs designed to serve diverse pupil needs; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D7CE9AA8-CE69-4ACE-9285-DAAA0CC538FD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A pupil’s residence or geographic location should not determine the quality of that pupil’s education; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E85E2520-4274-44E4-972D-6F1816996158"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, All pupils in the state, regardless of background, should have access to high-quality schools that meet their individual educational needs; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_263F6AF7-8039-4402-801B-EC7839CFD45C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School choice programs provide pupils and parents with access to high-quality schools and instructional models; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_EB0CEDDF-0051-4F22-BF9A-D60E385B3A46"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Parents and taxpayers who support the public education system should have meaningful options to choose the school that best serves their children; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_5E983768-A9D9-4D3A-BCF4-F7FB98E84F11"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School choice encourages parental engagement and strengthens partnerships between families, schools, and local communities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B358D537-C94D-4823-B3DA-B9A13173AB02"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, School choice is particularly important for low-income families and families in rural or geographically isolated areas who may have limited educational options; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_670CBEA4-302F-4F17-AFA5-23C01290135D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The state recognizes the many dedicated teaching professionals in public and nonpublic schools who are committed to educating the state’s pupils; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FAB38E34-A1E4-4917-884F-20286C48EB3A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The state has long embraced educational choice in the provision of higher education through a variety of public and independent institutions; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_365342CE-A8C9-4F57-8961-E34AC3D75001"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Parents, pupils, and educators throughout the nation annually recognize the importance of educational opportunity and effective school options for all children; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_6A8620E9-5118-4DB7-9E2E-F1492975EFEE"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates the week of January 25, 2026, to January 31, 2026, inclusive, as National School Choice Week; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_8DDA927F-40D7-40E4-A378-E70737B009AF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
